                    </div>
                    <span>For the most part I love this book. It is informative, and relatively simple to understand. This book is an "elementary approach to ideas and methods" for the whole field of mathmatics. In fact, this book is one of the reasons I changed my major to mathmatics.<p>However, there are two main problems with this book. First the quality of the print varies. Occasionally, whole sets of subscripts are blurred, which makes understanding the equation of the moment difficult, if not impossible.<p>Second, the order of steps for solving or understanding a problem are in an unexpected order, which is confusing. Often, I find that a difficult passage doesn't deal with difficult concepts, its just that the concepts are explained in an unusual way.<p>Aside from those problems, this is an extraordinary introduction to mathmatics.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Not an 'easy' read</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
